The words were not lacking in the letter from the WestLB Steering Committee to the employees of the house.
According to a union of entities of the financial institute of Düsseldorf with the Deka-Bank of Frankfurt, "the central financial markets institution of the financial group of the Sparkasse" could be constituted, according to the letter made public on Monday.
The WestLB would bring a "competence block" coupled with sustainable productivity in such a case.
All in all, such a relationship could be the decisive kick-off to other mergers in the Länder banking sector.
This is what it looks like when a policy committee wishes to demonstrate its ability to act in difficult times.
Because the wounded WestLB is still under strong pressure.
