"Sangre de Mayo", Garci's dared bet
Inspired by the stories of Benito Pérez Galdós, José Luis Garci recreates the famous battle of the Spanish against the French in "Sangre de mayo", which is the most ambitious film of his filmography with nearly 15 million euros in budget.
The filmmaker tried "to stage the many characters and illustrate the social analysis" that he has always admired in the work of the famous novelist, he explained today during the presentation of the film, with Quim Gutiérrez and Paula Echevarría at the head of the long list of actors.
The film lasting more than two and a half hours, "Sangre de mayo" will release in theaters next Friday, which will then become a television series for Telemadrid of more than four hours.
A great admirer of Galdós literature, José Luis Garci assures having realized with this shooting "a dream of a child" thanks to Esperanza Aguirre, who instructed him, three years ago, to shoot a commemorative film for the two hundred years of May 2 Madrid, something he has always accepted when the story was related to national historical facts.
The 15 million euros provided by the Municipality of Madrid constitute for Garci a "unique opportunity" to reproduce with the appropriate decorations and clothes the atmosphere of "a Spain that has made the wrong leader for the fight, since, the struggle for independence has led the people to rebellions under the reign of Ferdinand VII", he said.
But the filmmaker regrets not having obtained a funding as for the films "Captain Alatriste" or "The Ghosts of Goya" - more than double that obtained for "Sangre de mayo" - because he could not shoot some scenes written in a script signed by Horacio Valcárcel, with whom he collaborated for almost all his career.
The filmmaker of "Volver a empezar" influenced his usual way of working, on the staging of the actors, with whom he is used to rehearsing before starting the shooting and to whom he does not cast, since it seems "humiliating" to him and considers that "the role of the filmmaker is to go to the theater and the cinema to keep himself informed".
Many actors in "Sange de mayo" rehearse in front of the camera, such as Miguel Rellán, Carlos Larrañaga or Fernando Guillén Cuervo.
Four-time Oscar candidate (he won one), Garci considers that the three candidate films that represent Spain this year at the Hollywood Academy, "Sangre de mayo", "Seven French pool tables" and finally the winner, "The blind sunflowers", are not representative of the young Spanish cinema, "which deserves to be better known", he said.
With this film Garci does not expect a price.
“At first you think you’re working for posterity, then you realize that you’re only working for prosperity, and now you’re just making an extra movie,” Garci said after more than 30 years of professional career.
