What matters most is to raise consumer awareness and make this information public.
We must also review existing control systems, given the scientific opinion, so that they are fully effective and can follow new technologies
Brussels asked the Independent Scientific Committee to examine the problem, given the intensive use of portable musical equipment and the increase in the number of young people exposed to the noise they generate.
"Scientists-concluded the Ue- Executive confirm that there are good reasons to be concerned, and that the European Commission will now discuss with Member States and other interested parties what measures could possibly be taken to better protect children and adolescents, against exposure to noise from wearable music devices and similar devices.
